Checks divisibility using %
Counts occurrences using variables


Assignment (19/02/2026)
🎓 Student Data Manager
💻 Code:
students = {
    "Amit": 85,
    "Rahul": 78,
    "Sneha": 92,
    "Priya": 88,
    "Kiran": 74
}

# Calculate average
average = sum(students.values()) / len(students)

# Find topper
topper = max(students, key=students.get)

# Assign grades
grades = {}
for name, marks in students.items():
    if marks >= 90:
        grades[name] = "A"
    elif marks >= 75:
        grades[name] = "B"
    else:
        grades[name] = "C"

# Output
print("Average Marks:", average)
print("Topper:", topper)

print("\nGrades:")
for name in students:
    print(name, ":", grades[name])
Explanation
Uses dictionary to store student data
max() finds topper
sum() calculates average
Loop assigns grades


